message.content:
cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a controller for micro aerial vehicles (MAVs) and evaluates its performance on two different types of MAVs. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed controller is an evolving neuro-fuzzy controller that adapts to the environment and perturbations. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the stability of the proposed controller using Lyapunov stability analysis. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The controller is built upon a recently developed evolving neuro-fuzzy system known as parsimonious learning machine (PALM) and adopts new rule growing and pruning modules derived from the approximation of bias and variance. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed controller is a self-adaptive neuro-fuzzy controller that adapts its parameters in real-time without relying on user-defined thresholds.
